s\to\infty
 z^{-1}=\int_0^\infty\mathrm e^{-zs}\mathrm ds. 
 E[z^{-1}]=\int_0^\infty \prod_kE[\mathrm e^{-b_ky_ks}]\mathrm ds. 
 E[z^{-1}]=\int_0^\infty Q(s)\mathrm ds,\qquad Q(s)=\prod_k\frac1{1+b_ks}. 
 Q(s)=\sum_kc_k\frac{b_k}{1+b_ks}, 
 E[z^{-1}]=\sum_k\left.c_k\log(1+b_ks)\right|_0^\infty=\sum_kc_k\log b_k. 
 c_k=b_k^{m-2}\prod_{j\ne k}\frac1{b_k-b_j}, 
 E[z^{-1}]=\sum_k\left.c_k\log(1+b_ks)\right|_0^\infty=\sum_kb_k^{m-2}\log b_k\prod_{j\ne k}\frac1{b_k-b_j}. 
